-- Turkcell May Vie for Hellenic Telecom’s Bulgarian Unit
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   K o n s t a n t i n o v a
-- 2012-06-25T16:54:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/turkcell-may-vie-for-hellenic-telecom-s-bulgarian-unit-correct-.html
(Corrects to remove reference to units in other
countries.)  Vodafone Group Plc (VOD) ,  Turkcell
Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL) ,  Turkey ’s largest mobile phone company,
and Orange SA, controlled by  France Telecom SA (FTE) , may be among the
potential buyers of Globul, the Bulgarian mobile-phone unit of
Athens-based  Hellenic Telecommunications Organization SA (HTO) ,
Capital newspaper reported, without citing anyone.  Hellenic Telecommunications hired  Citigroup Inc. (C)  as
adviser.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
